Queen Daenerys I Targaryen, also known as Dany and Daenerys Stormborn, is a major character in the first, second, third, fourth, fifth, sixth and seventh seasons. She is played by starring cast member Emilia Clarke, and debuts in the series premiere. She is the younger sister of Rhaegar Targaryen and Viserys Targaryen, the aunt of Jon Snow, and the youngest child of King Aerys II Targaryen and Queen Rhaella Targaryen, who were both ousted from the Iron Throne during Robert Baratheon's rebellion.